This paper is primarily focused on the security of passwords and PINs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of videos and keystroke timing, which could be considered topics in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of videos also suggests the possibility of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) being used in the attack. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.IR) to improve the attack. Finally, the paper discusses the use of projectors and screens, which could be considered topics in multimedia (cs.MM).
